Content:
ARRR is a privacy coin built off a couple different ideas!! @ShadowKnight 
– Komodo Assetchain
– Independent blockchain

– Block reward: 256 PIRATE (ARRR)
– Block reward halves: every 388885 blocks – every 270 days

– Total supply of around 200 million PIRATE
– Mining algorithm: Equihash PoW
– TOR network supported.

Author: Dr4gonTrader#6152
Content: when opening the Agama wallet for ARRR spesifically, do I need to activate the coin each time I open the wallet, and sync the whole blockchain, then re-import my address with my private key? Is there no way to just open the wallet, and let it continue where it left of the last time I closed it?

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: You will need to sync the blockchain every time, yes. As new blocks are being created all the time. You shouldn't have to import your wallet everytime as it should be stored in your wallet.dat file on your computer. You may have to let the chain sync before it will show in your wallet though

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: It should only start syncing from the block it was last at though.
